This paper deals with the reliability function of a communication channel, specifically the discrete memoryless relay channel. This falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and communication (cs.COMM) sub-categories. The paper also uses techniques from source coding (cs.SI) and block coding (cs.DS), as well as considering the optimization of blocklengths (cs.NI).
